      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD represents a pinnacle of JDM engineering, maintained in museum-grade condition. The 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine exhibits perfect compression across all faces, delivering seamless boost through the factory-spec five-speed manual transmission. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, featuring its original double-wishbone suspension geometry and a Torsen limited-slip differential for neutral cornering dynamics. All critical cooling systems have been refreshed, and the vacuum-actuated turbo control system is fully synchronized for optimal transition. With zero oxidation on the undercarriage and a factory-fresh interior free of plastic degradation, this specimen is a turnkey investment for the serious collector.",
